verbose_text: For the reliability index, one obtains (7) beta = muGsigmaG, where the mean value, mu G, is the difference : (8) muG = muR-muS and the standard deviation, sigma G, is expressed by (9) sigmaG = sigmaR2-sigmaE2, where mu R, E are respective mean values of the structural resistance, R, or load effects, E, and sigma R, E, are the standard deviations for the structural resistance and load effect.
